      <div class="realpost"><div>
        <h2><a href="../post/790212932/great-moments-in-juxtaposition">Great Moments in Juxtaposition</a></h2>
        <blockquote>
  <p>Matt Taibbi on True/Slant called Brooks, among other things, a “spineless Beltway geek” on a “pencil-pusher’s eternal quest for macho cred” who “looks like a professional groveler/ass-kisser” and is “the kind of person who even in his spare time would pay a Leona Helmsley look-alike a thousand dollars to take a shit on his back.”</p>
  
  <p>Brooks says he agrees with some of the criticism. “Often you’ll read a commentary about the column and think, <em>That’s actually correct</em>,” he says.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>(<a href="http://nymag.com/news/media/67010/index3.html">David Brooks puff profile</a>, <em>NY Mag</em>)</p>
